        <![CDATA[
        <h2>What is eco-driving?</h2><br>
        Eco-driving is a method of driving a vehicle with the goal of using less fuel and having less of an impact on the environment.
        <br><br>
        <h2>What can be achieved by eco-driving?</h2><br>
        Benefits of eco-driving as cited by the U.S. Forest Service:
        <br>• Lower fuel use and costs
        <br>• Reduce emissions, including CO2
        <br>• Reduce vehicle wear
        <br>• Increase safety
        <br><br>
        <h2>Eco-driving techniques</h2>
        <br>• Don’t slam on the brakes
        <br>• Regulate your speed
        <br>• Reduce excess weight
        <br>• Optimize routing
        <br>• Avoid idling
        ]]>
